&lt;p&gt;Are you a &lt;strong&gt;Nurse Practitioner (NP)&lt;/strong&gt; or &lt;strong&gt;Physician Assistant (PA)&lt;/strong&gt; looking to level up your career in a thriving, supportive environment? Our bustling&lt;strong&gt; Skokie and Highland Park clinics&lt;/strong&gt; are growing!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaborative Urology Team:&lt;/strong&gt; Join a well-established group of 2 urologists committed to delivering top-tier, patient-focused care across &lt;strong&gt;Skokie and Highland Park.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Consistent and Supportive Schedule:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy a reliable &lt;strong&gt;Monday–Friday&lt;/strong&gt;, 8 am to 5 pm workweek that promotes work-life balance and long-term career satisfaction. &lt;strong&gt;The weekends are all yours!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Blended Care Environment:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy the best of both worlds with a primarily outpatient practice complemented by biweekly inpatient rounds, offering variety in your day while ensuring continuity of care across the patient journey.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Meaningful Patient Interactions:&lt;/strong&gt; See approximately &lt;strong&gt;25-30 patients per clinic-day&lt;/strong&gt;, while also focusing on pre-ops, post-ops, and consults—ensuring quality over quantity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why You’ll Love Skokie, IL - Where Diversity, Convenience &amp;amp; Community Come Together&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
